  "prompt": "Why do girls wear sports bras?",
  "response": "Girls wear sports bras for several reasons:\n\n1. **Support**: Sports bras provide necessary support during physical activities. They help minimize movement of the breasts, which can be uncomfortable or painful during exercise, especially for those with larger breasts.\n\n2. **Comfort**: They are typically made from stretchable, breathable materials that are designed for physical activity, making them more comfortable than regular bras.\n\n3. **Moisture management**: Many sports bras are made from moisture-wicking fabrics that help keep the body dry during sweaty workouts.\n\n4. **Reduced bounce**: Sports bras help reduce the bouncing of breasts during high-impact activities, which can help improve performance and reduce distraction.\n\n5. **Stability**: They offer a snug fit that helps stabilize the breast tissue, which can be beneficial during sports and exercise.\n\n6. **Versatility**: Sports bras can be worn not just during workouts but also as everyday clothing items, often under tank tops or loose shirts.\n\n7. **Fashion**: Many people also consider sports bras as a fashion statement or as a part of athleisure wear.\n\nOverall, wearing a sports bra helps girls and women feel more comfortable and confident while engaging in physical activities.",
